HEADWORD: Pinnatifid
<hw>Pin*nat"i*fid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pinnatus</ets> feathered + root of <ets>findere</ets> to split: cf.
F. <ets>pinnatifide</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Divided in a
pinnate manner, with the divisions not reaching to the midrib.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

